Test that URL-encoded path traversal attacks are blocked.

### SECURITY CRITICAL - P0

### Test Cases
- [ ] **Single URL encoding** - `%2e%2e/%2e%2e/etc/passwd` (.. = %2e%2e)
- [ ] **Double URL encoding** - `%252e%252e` (% = %25)
- [ ] **Mixed encoding** - `%2e./`, `.%2e/`, `..%2f`
- [ ] **Uppercase variants** - `%2E%2E`, `%2F`
- [ ] **Overlong UTF-8** - Invalid UTF-8 sequences that decode to `.`
- [ ] **Null byte injection** - `valid%00/../etc/passwd`
- [ ] **Backslash variants** - `..\\`, `%5c` (Windows)
- [ ] **Path separator confusion** - `..\/..\/`

### Implementation
```rust
#[test]
fn url_encoded_traversal_blocked() {
    let manifest = create_test_manifest_with_path("%2e%2e/%2e%2e/etc/passwd");
    let result = check_integrity(&site_dir, false);
    assert!(!result.passed, "URL-encoded traversal must be blocked");
    assert!(result.details.unwrap().contains("security violation"));
}

#[test]
